text.section:
As used in this section, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Casualty insurance" has the meaning set forth in KRS 304.5-070;
"Domestic violence and abuse" has the meaning set forth in KRS 403.720;
"Innocent co-insured" means an individual who did not cooperate in or contribute to the creation of the loss;
"Insurer" means an insurer licensed to write property or casualty insurance in Kentucky; and
"Property insurance" has the meaning set forth in KRS 304.5-050.
